@* Landscape-everywhere mandate: every non-combat screen (Bag, Bank, Shop,
   Loadout Editor, Hub, New Game) is built landscape-first per the UI bible
   ("Platform: mobile, landscape-only" + explicit left/right-panel specs for
   Loadout/Equipment) -- there is no working portrait layout for them, by
   design. A CSS-transform auto-rotate trick (like combat's .battle-fs) was
   tried here first but broke native scrolling for any of these screens with
   content taller than the viewport: rotating a flowing/stacking layout
   swaps which DOM axis is "visual vertical," so overflow bleeds sideways
   and the scrollbar ends up on the wrong axis. Combat never hit this
   because its HUD is entirely absolute-positioned, never scrolls. Blocking
   with a rotate prompt sidesteps the problem entirely and matches what the
   shipped (store-wrapped, OS-level landscape-locked) app will effectively
   enforce anyway -- see backlog.md's Distribution item. *@
<div class="rotate-overlay">
    <div class="rotate-overlay-icon">⟲</div>
    <p class="rotate-overlay-text">Rotate your device to landscape</p>
</div>
